rust-engine-container.tsx: entity-field-changed handler

The handler uses `prev.map(e => e.id !== id ? e : patched)` which only patches entities already present in the store. If a field-changed event arrives before entity-created (race condition during rapid writes), the patch is silently lost.

The old code did a full `get_entity` re-fetch when `fields` was present, which would upsert. The new architecture intentionally avoids re-fetch, making this race more consequential.

Suggestion: After the `.map()`, check if any entity was actually patched. If not (entity not in store), either log a warning or fetch-and-add as a recovery path. Example:
```ts
setEntitiesFor(entity_type, (prev) => {
  let found = false;
  const next = prev.map((e) => {
    if (e.id !== id) return e;
    found = true;
    // ... patch ...
  });
  if (!found) console.warn(`[entity-field-changed] entity ${entity_type}/${id} not in store, patch dropped`);
  return next;
});
```

Verification: Write a test that emits entity-field-changed before entity-created and verify the patch is not silently lost.

